messages.author: Station Earnings Report
messages.body:
Sector Economic Report

Sector vendor prices is currently at 100%, but company countermeasures protect YOU from being affected!

The station spending power is currently 0 Credits, and the crew's targeted allowance is at 25 Credits.

Large Drop! Vey-Medical 's latest product has seen major controversy, and resulted in a price drop for glass.
That's all from the Nanotrasen Economist Division.

messages.author: Central Command
messages.body:
Security level elevated.

The station has received reliable information about possible hostile activity on the station. Security staff may have weapons visible, random searches are permitted. A summary has been copied and printed to all communications consoles.

messages.author: Station Earnings Report
messages.body:
Sector Economic Report

Sector vendor prices is currently at 150%, but company countermeasures protect YOU from being affected!

The station spending power is currently 260 Credits, and the crew's targeted allowance is at 175 Credits.

Selling like Hotcakes! SolGov has just released a new product that is dominating the market for iron.
Selling like Hotcakes! Vey-Medical , in a surprise move, monopolized supply and has raised the price of uranium.
Selling like Hotcakes! SolGov has just released a new product that is dominating the market for silver.
Lockdown! Australicus Industrial Mining is being investigated by the Galactic Trade Commission, resulting in a halt of trade for silver.
Large Drop! Nakamura Engineering 's latest product has seen major controversy, and resulted in a price drop for iron.
Lockdown! MODular Solutions , in a stunning move, has been embargoed by TerraGov, resulting in a halt of trade of iron.
That's all from the Nanotrasen Economist Division.

messages.author: Nanotrasen Stock Report
messages.body:
Thank you for reading the Nanotrasen Stock Report. Due to quarterly earnings reports exceeding expectations by several percent, the Nanotrasen Incorporated stock has jumped 5%, one of the largest in months.

Originally published on: 9/26/2562
